# Build context for api/Dockerfile is the REPO ROOT (uv-workspace build). Keep it lean — the
# image only needs pyproject.toml, uv.lock, README.md, api/, and src/de_playground/. Everything
# below is irrelevant to that build (and .git/.venv/data are large or secret), so exclude it.
# NOTE: this applies to any build whose context is the repo root (api via `make api-push` and
# compose's `context: ..`); other images (spark/) build from their own dirs and are unaffected.

# VCS, envs, secrets, IDE, dev-container
.git
.github
.venv
.env
.idea
.devcontainer

# Caches + build/scratch artifacts
.mypy_cache
.pytest_cache
.ruff_cache
**/__pycache__
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info
dist
build
.coverage
coverage.xml
requirements-audit.txt

# Large or irrelevant to the api image
data
notebooks
docs
tests
sql
kibana
spark
compose
platform
observability
dags
jobs
